PERL INSTALLATION
=================
The following Perl modules must be installed from CPAN
	Image::ExifTool
		apt install -y libimage-exiftool-perl
	JSON::XS
		apt install -y libjson-xs-perl
	PDF::Create
		apt install -y libpdf-create-perl
	XML::LibXML
		apt install -y libxml-libxml-perl
	XML::Writer
		apt install -y libxml-writer-perl



PORTAL - Monitor file access
============================
Install
    apt install inotify-tools

Watch for any event in any file or directories under the 'airwave' directory
    inotifywait /srv/visualsaas/instances/airwave -r -d -o /var/log/breato/airwave-watch.log

Watch for specified events in any file or directores under the 'airwave' directory
    inotifywait /srv/visualsaas/instances/airwave -r -d -o /var/log/breato/airwave-watch.log -e modify -e move -e create -e delete



VAGRANT and VIRTUALBOX
======================
Installation
	sudo apt install virtualbox
	sudo apt install vagrant
	vi /usr/lib/ruby/vendor_ruby/vagrant/bundler.rb
		replace line 275 with Gem::Specification.reset
	sudo vagrant plugin install vagrant-hostsupdater

Patch Network Config
	dmesg | grep renamed
		[0.774551] r8169 0000:02:00.0 enp2s0: renamed from eth0
	sudo vi /etc/network/interfaces.d/enp2s0.cfg
		auto enp2s0
		iface enp2s0 inet dhcp
	sudo systemctl restart networking.service

Upgrade
	vagrant box update

Options
	vagrant suspend|halt|destroy|reload|provision|ssh

Configure
	cd ~/Drive/Software/Airwave
	mkdir vagrant
	cd vagrant
	vi provision.sh
	vi Vagrantfile

Run
	cd ~/Drive/Software/Airwave/vagrant
	vagrant destroy
	vagrant up
	<FAILS with eth1 error>
	vagrant ssh
	sudo vi /etc/network/interfaces
		auto eth1
		iface eth1 inet manual
	sudo vi /etc/hosts
		192.168.1.176 dev.very-api.net
	exit
	vagrant provision



COMPILING AIRSHIP
=================
cd ~/Drive/Software/Airwave/vagrant
vagrant destroy
vagrant up							# brings up ubuntu & debian
vagrant ssh debian
cd /vagrant/airware/airship

sudo ln -s /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/qtchooser/qt5.conf /etc/xdg/qtchooser/default.conf

./deb-build.sh
